SUMMARY:🔥 AU ABS: Wage Price Index\, Australia\, March 2026
DESCRIPTION:Source: AU ABS\nImpact: high\nSource: AU ABS\nImpact: high\nS
 ource: AU ABS\nImpact: high\nOfficial ABS latest release page\n\nExplain
 er:\n• What it is: Wage Price Index / Average Earnings\n\n• Measures
 : Change in wages and earnings.\n\n• Usual market effect: Higher-than-
 forecast wage growth can be bullish for the local currency if traders ex
 pect stronger inflation pressure and tighter central-bank policy.\n\n•
  Why traders care: Wage growth can feed into inflation and is closely wa
 tched by central banks.\n\n• Frequency: Monthly or quarterly depending
  on release.\n\n• Notes: Strong wages can be positive for consumers bu
 t can also increase inflation pressure.\n\n• Acronyms: WPI = Wage Pric
 e Index.\n\nOfficial source: https://www.abs.gov.au/statistics/economy/p
 rice-indexes-and-inflation/wage-price-index-australia/mar-2026\n\nExplai
 ner:\n• What it is: Wage Price Index / Average Earnings\n\n• Measure
 s: Change in wages and earnings.\n\n• Usual market effect: Higher-than
 -forecast wage growth can be bullish for the local currency if traders e
 xpect stronger inflation pressure and tighter central-bank policy.\n\n
 • Why traders care: Wage growth can feed into inflation and is closely
  watched by central banks.\n\n• Frequency: Monthly or quarterly depend
 ing on release.\n\n• Notes: Strong wages can be positive for consumers
  but can also increase inflation pressure.\n\n• Acronyms: WPI = Wage P
 rice Index.\n\nOfficial source: https://www.abs.gov.au/statistics/econom
 y/price-indexes-and-inflation/wage-price-index-australia/mar-2026\n\nExp
 lainer:\n• What it is: Wage Price Index / Average Earnings\n\n• Meas
 ures: Change in wages and earnings.\n\n• Usual market effect: Higher-t
 han-forecast wage growth can be bullish for the local currency if trader
 s expect stronger inflation pressure and tighter central-bank policy.\n\
 n• Why traders care: Wage growth can feed into inflation and is closel
 y watched by central banks.\n\n• Frequency: Monthly or quarterly depen
 ding on release.\n\n• Notes: Strong wages can be positive for consumer
 s but can also increase inflation pressure.\n\n• Acronyms: WPI = Wage 
 Price Index.\n\nOfficial source: https://www.abs.gov.au/statistics/econo
 my/price-indexes-and-inflation/wage-price-index-australia/mar-2026
