SUMMARY:🔥 US Fed: FOMC Interest Rate Decision
DESCRIPTION:Source: US Fed\nImpact: high\nSource: US Fed\nImpact: high\nS
 ource: US Fed\nImpact: high\nSource: US Fed\nImpact: high\nOfficial Fede
 ral Reserve monthly calendar FOMC meeting entry.\n\nExplainer:\n• What
  it is: Central Bank Rate Decision\n\n• Measures: Interest-rate decisi
 on\, policy statement and guidance from the central bank.\n\n• Usual m
 arket effect: More hawkish-than-expected guidance is usually bullish for
  the local currency and bearish for bonds. More dovish-than-expected gui
 dance is usually bearish for the currency and bullish for bonds.\n\n• 
 Why traders care: Central-bank decisions directly affect interest rates\
 , currency valuation\, bond yields and equity risk appetite.\n\n• Freq
 uency: Scheduled several times per year.\n\n• Notes: The market often 
 reacts not only to the rate decision\, but also to the statement\, forec
 asts\, press conference and tone.\n\n• Acronyms: FOMC = Federal Open M
 arket Committee\; RBA = Reserve Bank of Australia.\n\nOfficial source: h
 ttps://www.federalreserve.gov/newsevents/2026-june.htm\n\nExplainer:\n
 • What it is: Central Bank Rate Decision\n\n• Measures: Interest-rat
 e decision\, policy statement and guidance from the central bank.\n\n•
  Usual market effect: More hawkish-than-expected guidance is usually bul
 lish for the local currency and bearish for bonds. More dovish-than-expe
 cted guidance is usually bearish for the currency and bullish for bonds.
 \n\n• Why traders care: Central-bank decisions directly affect interes
 t rates\, currency valuation\, bond yields and equity risk appetite.\n\n
 • Frequency: Scheduled several times per year.\n\n• Notes: The marke
 t often reacts not only to the rate decision\, but also to the statement
 \, forecasts\, press conference and tone.\n\n• Acronyms: FOMC = Federa
 l Open Market Committee\; RBA = Reserve Bank of Australia.\n\nOfficial s
 ource: https://www.federalreserve.gov/newsevents/2026-june.htm\n\nExplai
 ner:\n• What it is: Central Bank Rate Decision\n\n• Measures: Intere
 st-rate decision\, policy statement and guidance from the central bank.\
 n\n• Usual market effect: More hawkish-than-expected guidance is usual
 ly bullish for the local currency and bearish for bonds. More dovish-tha
 n-expected guidance is usually bearish for the currency and bullish for 
 bonds.\n\n• Why traders care: Central-bank decisions directly affect i
 nterest rates\, currency valuation\, bond yields and equity risk appetit
 e.\n\n• Frequency: Scheduled several times per year.\n\n• Notes: The
  market often reacts not only to the rate decision\, but also to the sta
 tement\, forecasts\, press conference and tone.\n\n• Acronyms: FOMC = 
 Federal Open Market Committee\; RBA = Reserve Bank of Australia.\n\nOffi
 cial source: https://www.federalreserve.gov/newsevents/2026-june.htm\n\n
 Explainer:\n• What it is: Central Bank Rate Decision\n\n• Measures: 
 Interest-rate decision\, policy statement and guidance from the central 
 bank.\n\n• Usual market effect: More hawkish-than-expected guidance is
  usually bullish for the local currency and bearish for bonds. More dovi
 sh-than-expected guidance is usually bearish for the currency and bullis
 h for bonds.\n\n• Why traders care: Central-bank decisions directly af
 fect interest rates\, currency valuation\, bond yields and equity risk a
 ppetite.\n\n• Frequency: Scheduled several times per year.\n\n• Note
 s: The market often reacts not only to the rate decision\, but also to t
 he statement\, forecasts\, press conference and tone.\n\n• Acronyms: F
 OMC = Federal Open Market Committee\; RBA = Reserve Bank of Australia.\n
 \nOfficial source: https://www.federalreserve.gov/newsevents/2026-june.h
 tm
