SUMMARY:🔥 AU ABS: Producer Price Indexes\, Australia\, June 2026
DESCRIPTION:Source: AU ABS\nImpact: high\nSource: AU ABS\nImpact: high\nS
 ource: AU ABS\nImpact: high\nSource: AU ABS\nImpact: high\nOfficial ABS 
 series page release date. Time zone shown by ABS: AEST.\n\nExplainer:\n
 • What it is: Producer Price Index\n\n• Measures: Change in prices r
 eceived by producers for goods and services.\n\n• Usual market effect:
  Higher-than-forecast PPI can be bullish for the local currency if trade
 rs expect producer inflation to flow through to consumer inflation.\n\n
 • Why traders care: PPI can provide an early signal of inflation press
 ure before it reaches consumers.\n\n• Frequency: Monthly in the US. Qu
 arterly in Australia.\n\n• Notes: PPI is usually less market-moving th
 an CPI\, but it can still matter when inflation is the main macro theme.
 \n\n• Acronyms: PPI = Producer Price Index.\n\nOfficial source: https:
 //www.abs.gov.au/statistics/economy/price-indexes-and-inflation/producer
 -price-indexes-australia\n\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Producer Price I
 ndex\n\n• Measures: Change in prices received by producers for goods a
 nd services.\n\n• Usual market effect: Higher-than-forecast PPI can be
  bullish for the local currency if traders expect producer inflation to 
 flow through to consumer inflation.\n\n• Why traders care: PPI can pro
 vide an early signal of inflation pressure before it reaches consumers.\
 n\n• Frequency: Monthly in the US. Quarterly in Australia.\n\n• Note
 s: PPI is usually less market-moving than CPI\, but it can still matter 
 when inflation is the main macro theme.\n\n• Acronyms: PPI = Producer 
 Price Index.\n\nOfficial source: https://www.abs.gov.au/statistics/econo
 my/price-indexes-and-inflation/producer-price-indexes-australia\n\nExpla
 iner:\n• What it is: Producer Price Index\n\n• Measures: Change in p
 rices received by producers for goods and services.\n\n• Usual market 
 effect: Higher-than-forecast PPI can be bullish for the local currency i
 f traders expect producer inflation to flow through to consumer inflatio
 n.\n\n• Why traders care: PPI can provide an early signal of inflation
  pressure before it reaches consumers.\n\n• Frequency: Monthly in the 
 US. Quarterly in Australia.\n\n• Notes: PPI is usually less market-mov
 ing than CPI\, but it can still matter when inflation is the main macro 
 theme.\n\n• Acronyms: PPI = Producer Price Index.\n\nOfficial source: 
 https://www.abs.gov.au/statistics/economy/price-indexes-and-inflation/pr
 oducer-price-indexes-australia\n\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Producer P
 rice Index\n\n• Measures: Change in prices received by producers for g
 oods and services.\n\n• Usual market effect: Higher-than-forecast PPI 
 can be bullish for the local currency if traders expect producer inflati
 on to flow through to consumer inflation.\n\n• Why traders care: PPI c
 an provide an early signal of inflation pressure before it reaches consu
 mers.\n\n• Frequency: Monthly in the US. Quarterly in Australia.\n\n
 • Notes: PPI is usually less market-moving than CPI\, but it can still
  matter when inflation is the main macro theme.\n\n• Acronyms: PPI = P
 roducer Price Index.\n\nOfficial source: https://www.abs.gov.au/statisti
 cs/economy/price-indexes-and-inflation/producer-price-indexes-australia
