 l market effect: Higher-than-forecast inflation is usually bullish for t
 he local currency and bearish for bonds\, because markets may price in h
 igher interest rates.\n\n• Why traders care: CPI is one of the most wa
 tched inflation indicators because it can quickly shift central-bank rat
 e expectations.\n\n• Frequency: US CPI is monthly. Australian CPI has 
 both monthly indicator releases and quarterly CPI releases.\n\n• Notes
 : Core CPI removes volatile items such as food and energy to give a clea
 ner read on underlying inflation pressure.\n\n• Acronyms: CPI = Consum
 er Price Index.\n\nOfficial source: https://www.abs.gov.au/statistics/ec
 onomy/price-indexes-and-inflation/consumer-price-index-australia\n\nExpl
 ainer:\n• What it is: Consumer Price Index\n\n• Measures: Change in 
 the prices paid by consumers for a basket of goods and services.\n\n• 
 Usual market effect: Higher-than-forecast inflation is usually bullish f
 or the local currency and bearish for bonds\, because markets may price 
 in higher interest rates.\n\n• Why traders care: CPI is one of the mos
 t watched inflation indicators because it can quickly shift central-bank
  rate expectations.\n\n• Frequency: US CPI is monthly. Australian CPI 
 has both monthly indicator releases and quarterly CPI releases.\n\n• N
 otes: Core CPI removes volatile items such as food and energy to give a 
 cleaner read on underlying inflation pressure.\n\n• Acronyms: CPI = Co
 nsumer Price Index.\n\nOfficial source: https://www.abs.gov.au/statistic
 s/economy/price-indexes-and-inflation/consumer-price-index-australia\n\n
 Explainer:\n• What it is: Consumer Price Index\n\n• Measures: Change
  in the prices paid by consumers for a basket of goods and services.\n\n
 • Usual market effect: Higher-than-forecast inflation is usually bulli
 sh for the local currency and bearish for bonds\, because markets may pr
 ice in higher interest rates.\n\n• Why traders care: CPI is one of the
  most watched inflation indicators because it can quickly shift central-
 bank rate expectations.\n\n• Frequency: US CPI is monthly. Australian 
 CPI has both monthly indicator releases and quarterly CPI releases.\n\n
 • Notes: Core CPI removes volatile items such as food and energy to gi
 ve a cleaner read on underlying inflation pressure.\n\n• Acronyms: CPI
  = Consumer Price Index.\n\nOfficial source: https://www.abs.gov.au/stat
 istics/economy/price-indexes-and-inflation/consumer-price-index-australi
 a
