 iod\n\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Producer Price Index\n\n• Measures:
  Change in prices received by producers for goods and services.\n\n• U
 sual market effect: Higher-than-forecast PPI can be bullish for the loca
 l currency if traders expect producer inflation to flow through to consu
 mer inflation.\n\n• Why traders care: PPI can provide an early signal 
 of inflation pressure before it reaches consumers.\n\n• Frequency: Mon
 thly in the US. Quarterly in Australia.\n\n• Notes: PPI is usually les
 s market-moving than CPI\, but it can still matter when inflation is the
  main macro theme.\n\n• Acronyms: PPI = Producer Price Index.\n\nOffic
 ial source: https://www.abs.gov.au/release-calendar/future-releases/2026
