 : Higher-than-forecast wage growth can be bullish for the local currency
  if traders expect stronger inflation pressure and tighter central-bank 
 policy.\n\n• Why traders care: Wage growth can feed into inflation and
  is closely watched by central banks.\n\n• Frequency: Monthly or quart
 erly depending on release.\n\n• Notes: Strong wages can be positive fo
 r consumers but can also increase inflation pressure.\n\n• Acronyms: W
 PI = Wage Price Index.\n\nOfficial source: https://www.abs.gov.au/releas
 e-calendar/future-releases/202611\n\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Wage Pr
 ice Index / Average Earnings\n\n• Measures: Change in wages and earnin
 gs.\n\n• Usual market effect: Higher-than-forecast wage growth can be 
 bullish for the local currency if traders expect stronger inflation pres
 sure and tighter central-bank policy.\n\n• Why traders care: Wage grow
 th can feed into inflation and is closely watched by central banks.\n\n
 • Frequency: Monthly or quarterly depending on release.\n\n• Notes: 
 Strong wages can be positive for consumers but can also increase inflati
 on pressure.\n\n• Acronyms: WPI = Wage Price Index.\n\nOfficial source
 : https://www.abs.gov.au/release-calendar/future-releases/202611\n\nExpl
 ainer:\n• What it is: Wage Price Index / Average Earnings\n\n• Measu
 res: Change in wages and earnings.\n\n• Usual market effect: Higher-th
 an-forecast wage growth can be bullish for the local currency if traders
  expect stronger inflation pressure and tighter central-bank policy.\n\n
 • Why traders care: Wage growth can feed into inflation and is closely
  watched by central banks.\n\n• Frequency: Monthly or quarterly depend
 ing on release.\n\n• Notes: Strong wages can be positive for consumers
  but can also increase inflation pressure.\n\n• Acronyms: WPI = Wage P
 rice Index.\n\nOfficial source: https://www.abs.gov.au/release-calendar/
 future-releases/202611\n\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Wage Price Index /
  Average Earnings\n\n• Measures: Change in wages and earnings.\n\n• 
 Usual market effect: Higher-than-forecast wage growth can be bullish for
  the local currency if traders expect stronger inflation pressure and ti
 ghter central-bank policy.\n\n• Why traders care: Wage growth can feed
  into inflation and is closely watched by central banks.\n\n• Frequenc
 y: Monthly or quarterly depending on release.\n\n• Notes: Strong wages
  can be positive for consumers but can also increase inflation pressure.
 \n\n• Acronyms: WPI = Wage Price Index.\n\nOfficial source: https://ww
 w.abs.gov.au/release-calendar/future-releases/202611
