SUMMARY:🔥 US Fed: FOMC Interest Rate Decision
DESCRIPTION:Source: US Fed\nImpact: high\nSource: US Fed\nImpact: high\nS
 ource: US Fed\nImpact: high\nSource: US Fed\nImpact: high\nOfficial Fede
 ral Reserve monthly calendar FOMC meeting entry.\n\nExplainer:\n• What
  it is: Central Bank Rate Decision\n\n• Measures: Interest-rate decisi
 on\, policy statement and guidance from the central bank.\n\n• Usual m
 arket effect: More hawkish-than-expected guidance is usually bullish for
  the local currency and bearish for bonds. More dovish-than-expected gui
 dance is usually bearish for the currency and bullish for bonds.\n\n• 
 Why traders care: Central-bank decisions directly affect interest rates\
 , currency valuation\, bond yields and equity risk appetite.\n\n• Freq
 uency: Scheduled several times per year.\n\n• Notes: The market often 
 reacts not only to the rate decision\, but also to the statement\, forec
 asts\, press conference and tone.\n\n• Acronyms: FOMC = Federal Open M
 arket Committee\; RBA = Reserve Bank of Australia.\n\nOfficial source: h
 ttps://www.federalreserve.gov/newsevents/2026-december.htm\n\nExplainer:
 \n• What it is: Central Bank Rate Decision\n\n• Measures: Interest-r
 ate decision\, policy statement and guidance from the central bank.\n\n
 • Usual market effect: More hawkish-than-expected guidance is usually 
 bullish for the local currency and bearish for bonds. More dovish-than-e
 xpected guidance is usually bearish for the currency and bullish for bon
 ds.\n\n• Why traders care: Central-bank decisions directly affect inte
 rest rates\, currency valuation\, bond yields and equity risk appetite.\
 n\n• Frequency: Scheduled several times per year.\n\n• Notes: The ma
 rket often reacts not only to the rate decision\, but also to the statem
 ent\, forecasts\, press conference and tone.\n\n• Acronyms: FOMC = Fed
 eral Open Market Committee\; RBA = Reserve Bank of Australia.\n\nOfficia
 l source: https://www.federalreserve.gov/newsevents/2026-december.htm\n\
 nExplainer:\n• What it is: Central Bank Rate Decision\n\n• Measures:
  Interest-rate decision\, policy statement and guidance from the central
  bank.\n\n• Usual market effect: More hawkish-than-expected guidance i
 s usually bullish for the local currency and bearish for bonds. More dov
 ish-than-expected guidance is usually bearish for the currency and bulli
 sh for bonds.\n\n• Why traders care: Central-bank decisions directly a
 ffect interest rates\, currency valuation\, bond yields and equity risk 
 appetite.\n\n• Frequency: Scheduled several times per year.\n\n• Not
 es: The market often reacts not only to the rate decision\, but also to 
 the statement\, forecasts\, press conference and tone.\n\n• Acronyms: 
 FOMC = Federal Open Market Committee\; RBA = Reserve Bank of Australia.\
 n\nOfficial source: https://www.federalreserve.gov/newsevents/2026-decem
 ber.htm\n\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Central Bank Rate Decision\n\n•
  Measures: Interest-rate decision\, policy statement and guidance from t
 he central bank.\n\n• Usual market effect: More hawkish-than-expected 
 guidance is usually bullish for the local currency and bearish for bonds
 . More dovish-than-expected guidance is usually bearish for the currency
  and bullish for bonds.\n\n• Why traders care: Central-bank decisions 
 directly affect interest rates\, currency valuation\, bond yields and eq
 uity risk appetite.\n\n• Frequency: Scheduled several times per year.\
 n\n• Notes: The market often reacts not only to the rate decision\, bu
 t also to the statement\, forecasts\, press conference and tone.\n\n• 
 Acronyms: FOMC = Federal Open Market Committee\; RBA = Reserve Bank of A
 ustralia.\n\nOfficial source: https://www.federalreserve.gov/newsevents/
 2026-december.htm
